## ğŸ¨ Key Features Explained

### Dynamic Section Loading
The portfolio uses a modular approach where sections are loaded dynamically:

```javascript
// Section files mapping
const sectionFiles = {
    'about': 'sections/about.html',
    'skills': 'sections/skills.html',
    // ... other sections
};
```

### Resume Download Functionality
Integrated PDF generation for resume download:
- Professional formatting matching actual resume
- Print-optimized CSS
- One-click download feature

### Responsive Design
- Mobile-first approach
- Flexible grid layouts
- Adaptive navigation
- Touch-friendly interactions

## ğŸš€ Deployment

### Vercel Deployment

1. Connect GitHub Repository
   - Login to [Vercel](https://vercel.com)
   - Import your GitHub repository
   - Configure build settings (automatic for static sites)

2. Environment Setup
   - No special configuration needed for static site
   - Automatic deployments on git push

3. Custom Domain (Optional)
   - Add custom domain in Vercel dashboard
   - Configure DNS settings

### Alternative Deployment Options

- Netlify: Drag and drop deployment
- GitHub Pages: Enable in repository settings
- Firebase Hosting: `firebase deploy`

## ğŸ”§ Customization

### Adding New Sections
1. Create new HTML file in `sections/` directory
2. Add section to `sectionFiles` object in `index.html`
3. Update navigation links

### Styling Modifications
- Main styles in `styles.css`
- CSS custom properties for easy theming
- Responsive breakpoints defined

### Content Updates
- Modify individual section files
- Update project information
- Add new images to `images/` directory

## ğŸ“Š Performance Optimizations

- Lazy Loading: Sections loaded on demand
- Optimized Images: Compressed image assets
- Minimal Dependencies: Vanilla JavaScript for speed
- CSS Animations: Hardware-accelerated transitions
- Code Splitting: Modular architecture

